name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: ...and sadly serves as a grim reminder of the importance of following public health orders and guidance so we can reduce the number of serious illnesses and deaths in our state. Jennie and I extend our thoughts and prayers to this gentleman’s family and friends.

name: David B Wheeler, MD, PhD
tweet: Thank you for making the case for pcr and antibody testing in Wyoming. Extensive testing and contact tracing is the most efficient way to get us back in business. We appreciate your efforts to encourage continued social distancing as we keep climbing to the top of the curve.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: Now is not the time to travel to Wyoming. We are focused on protect the health of our citizens and the resources of our rural healthcare facilities. Stay home and stay safe. https://governor.wyo.gov/media/news-releases/2020-news-releases/governor-state-health-officer-extend-statewide-public-health-orders-throug …

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: I have also issued a directive requiring any individual coming to Wyoming for a non-work-related purpose to immediately self-quarantine for 14 days. Visitors from neighboring states have strained the resources of our communities and put public health at risk.

name: Amy Surdam
tweet: Dear @GovernorGordon, thank you for your constant kindness and leadership. You are a wonderful governor. There are a lot of people who are not listening and are putting others at risk. Please issue a stay at home order so that we can eliminate this in our state faster.

name: Bradley Rettler
tweet: Actually it’s up to you. By failing to order NOW the shelter-in-place that’s coming, there will be more cases and more deaths.

name: Amy Surdam
tweet: Please issue a shelter in place order. It is inevitable. The sooner you order it the sooner we will contain the virus. Delaying is hurting our workforce who is already out of work and our people.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: This is how we can save lives and protect people’s health.  I also understand the ongoing strain these measures are having on businesses, workers and Wyoming communities but it is critical each of us takes these steps now.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: Now is not the time to be evicting individuals who may have recently become unemployed. It’s important for us all to work together and support one-another during these difficult times. If you are struggling, Wyoming 211 has a list of statewide resources.  https://wy211.communityos.org/

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 9/9 Shop for groceries if you need to, get food delivered from your favorite restaurant, support your local business with a gift card purchase. But please practice social distancing measures during this critical time. #COVID19WY

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 8/9 By limiting travel and face-to-face contact now, we reduce the potential to overwhelm our rural healthcare facilities and cause unnecessary deaths ahead. Wyoming’s rural nature does not protect us from impacts.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 7/9 Like the rest of America, Wyoming’s access to testing supplies is limited. Our best tool right now for slowing the spread of this disease is practicing social distancing measures.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 6/9 ...the enormity of the public health challenge facing us and respond to it. COVID-19 may seem far away, but it is here. Our neighboring states are all experiencing the same escalation in the number of positive cases as we are.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 5/9 I am a businessman and understand full well what the consequences would be of closures. I know that the worst impacts would fall on those least able to absorb it.   As confirmed cases have grown from 1 to 23 in a week, spanning 8 counties, we should be honest about...

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 4/9 ...that unemployment benefits are readily accessible, that those who are food insecure are fed, and that our essential business functions are preserved. I am proud of my Wyoming heritage and the fact that we can serve as a beacon for our nation.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 3/9 We are in this for the long haul and we will emerge stronger for this test, and I will always be guided by my concern for the health and safety of the people of Wyoming. folks at the state are working 24/7 to assure that proper supplies arrive as quickly as possible...

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 2/9 From the beginning, I have emphasized that the challenge we are facing represents two threats: disease and economic harm.  I have been very clear that both are important.  I believe firmly we must do the right thing, do it right away, and do it the right way.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: This is Wyoming, where we are all neighbors. While social distancing should be a priority, it should not keep us from helping one another out. I am thinking of our first responders and healthcare workers  who may be without child care. This is a time to help one another out.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: This is an attempt to allow schools and communities to prepare to operate in a way that mitigates community spread of COVID-19 and minimizes negative economic impacts locally and statewide.
